    "long_instructions": "##Histograms\r\n\r\nSometimes, if we put our data into buckets, we can get some clearer insights.\r\n\r\nNeed a new copy of the dataset? [Google Sheets Link](https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1hZ9K6TX3CklY56b4NQAABD5UqYEEGBeP64UQQ7-OnvU/edit?gid=1782593835#gid=1782593835)\r\n\r\n###**Do This**\r\n1. Sort the data by \"Type\"\r\n2. Make two histograms based on the \"Top_Speed\" column: one for wooden and one for steel.\r\n3. Do wooden coasters have higher top speeds than steel coasters? How can you tell?\r\n\r\n",
